WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.023 --> 00:00:02.897
Previously on AMC's
"Better Call Saul"...

2
00:00:02.922 --> 00:00:05.163
Free. I'll shoot the spot for free.

3
00:00:05.188 --> 00:00:06.255
For free?

4
00:00:06.280 --> 00:00:07.892
You're losing money.

5
00:00:07.894 --> 00:00:09.060
My brother is sick.

6
00:00:09.062 --> 00:00:11.095
He's making mistakes with his clients.

7
00:00:11.097 --> 00:00:12.730
You're not gonna do anything. are you?

8
00:00:12.732 --> 00:00:14.140
To new beginnings.

9
00:00:14.165 --> 00:00:16.734
I need to see Dr. Cruz
as soon as possible.

10
00:00:16.736 --> 00:00:18.773
The man killed for
helping the truck driver.

11
00:00:18.798 --> 00:00:21.389
You are trying to correct
something which cannot be corrected.

12
00:00:21.414 --> 00:00:23.242
Hector wants to use my dad's business.

13
00:00:23.267 --> 00:00:26.368
If you manage to pull this
off and switch those pills.

14
00:00:26.393 --> 00:00:27.678
switch them back.

15
00:00:27.680 --> 00:00:30.104
I'm gonna need one more thing from you.

16
00:00:51.688 --> 00:00:53.688
Let there be light.

17
00:00:53.691 --> 00:00:56.125
And then there was light.

18
00:00:59.462 --> 00:01:02.127
Geez. Will you look at this...

19
00:01:06.404 --> 00:01:09.208
That's where your mom used to work.

20
00:01:09.233 --> 00:01:11.272
Right back there. doin' the books.

21
00:01:11.297 --> 00:01:13.007
Yeah. Whatever.

22
00:01:17.772 --> 00:01:19.880
Hey. remember when we
used to ditch fourth.

23
00:01:19.905 --> 00:01:21.350
come in the back door?

24
00:01:21.352 --> 00:01:23.679
Tell your folks it was a free period.

25
00:01:23.704 --> 00:01:25.591
O'Dell's Algebra Two.

26
00:01:25.616 --> 00:01:27.366
Mr. O'Dell.

27
00:01:27.391 --> 00:01:29.625
Man. that guy was a butthole.

28
00:01:29.627 --> 00:01:32.094
And your mom. you know. I
think she knew we were skipping.

29
00:01:32.096 --> 00:01:33.624
but she'd always stop what she was doing

30
00:01:33.649 --> 00:01:35.354
and gimme a pack of Little Debbie's.

31
00:01:35.379 --> 00:01:38.934
Ahh. Think all those Little
Debbie's put them out of business.

32
00:01:40.250 --> 00:01:42.225
Hey. how'd you get up
there when you were a kid?

33
00:01:42.227 --> 00:01:44.756
Couple of milk crates. you know?

34
00:01:47.833 --> 00:01:49.666
Ohh.

35
00:01:57.309 --> 00:01:58.875
All right.

36
00:02:01.880 --> 00:02:05.125
No. No. No. Nope.

37
00:02:05.150 --> 00:02:06.455
Ah.

38
00:02:08.177 --> 00:02:09.501
Boom.

39
00:02:09.526 --> 00:02:11.308
Indian Head penny.

40
00:02:11.333 --> 00:02:13.323
All right? That's
worth about three bucks.

41
00:02:13.325 --> 00:02:15.642
We polish it up. run the coin game...

42
00:02:15.667 --> 00:02:17.760
Nice. We get 150 bucks. easy.

43
00:02:17.762 --> 00:02:20.707
$150? We got a $110 for a
plain vanilla half dollar.

44
00:02:20.732 --> 00:02:22.732
This... this is actually rare.

45
00:02:22.734 --> 00:02:24.305
I mean. you can see it.

46
00:02:24.352 --> 00:02:26.836
- $300. easy.
- Oh. $300?

47
00:02:26.838 --> 00:02:29.014
Me likey. Yeah.

48
00:02:29.039 --> 00:02:32.578
Now you're gonna tell me what your
coin collection was doin' up there.

49
00:02:32.603 --> 00:02:34.102
Uh...

50
00:02:35.422 --> 00:02:37.516
It's a long story.

51
00:02:37.541 --> 00:02:41.551
Um... let's get outta here.

52
00:02:52.750 --> 00:02:56.199
- All right. Now. Let's hit it.
- No. there might be another one.

53
00:02:56.201 --> 00:02:57.567
All right.

54
00:02:57.569 --> 00:02:58.801
Then give.

55
00:02:58.803 --> 00:03:01.031
What's the deal with the coins?

56
00:03:04.976 --> 00:03:06.367
Well. uh...

57
00:03:07.775 --> 00:03:11.061
I was what? Uh. 12 or so?

58
00:03:11.086 --> 00:03:12.549
I was working the register.

59
00:03:12.551 --> 00:03:15.785
Guy comes in. buys a box of Ivory Flakes

60
00:03:15.787 --> 00:03:19.656
and a sixer of Old Style.

61
00:03:21.508 --> 00:03:24.817
He pays with a couple bucks and...

62
00:03:25.297 --> 00:03:26.563
this.

63
00:03:26.565 --> 00:03:28.998
The second I see it.
I know what it is...

64
00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.401
it's a George Washington silver.

65
00:03:31.403 --> 00:03:34.404
I tell my dad. "Pop.
this quarter is rare.

66
00:03:34.429 --> 00:03:37.403
It's worth four bucks."

67
00:03:37.817 --> 00:03:39.342
Barely get the words outta my mouth...

68
00:03:39.367 --> 00:03:42.489
he hightails it outta
here to give it back.

69
00:03:42.514 --> 00:03:43.872
He can't find the guy.

70
00:03:43.897 --> 00:03:46.015
so he tapes it to the
side of the register...

71
00:03:46.017 --> 00:03:47.593
he's hoping...

72
00:03:47.618 --> 00:03:49.640
that this guy will come back...

73
00:03:49.665 --> 00:03:52.021
so we can return it.

74
00:03:52.023 --> 00:03:54.023
After about a week.
he starts talking about

75
00:03:54.025 --> 00:03:56.259
givin' it to Father
Mahoney for the poor box.

76
00:03:56.261 --> 00:03:58.005
so I make it disappear.

77
00:03:58.030 --> 00:04:00.630
And after that. every day after
school. I'm checking the till.

78
00:04:00.655 --> 00:04:02.013
You know. something catches my eye.

79
00:04:02.038 --> 00:04:05.268
I stick it in the box. put
it up there for good luck.

80
00:04:06.638 --> 00:04:08.805
So much for good luck.

81
00:04:10.334 --> 00:04:13.372
It was a cryin' shame
they lost this place.

82
00:04:13.397 --> 00:04:16.200
They never shoulda bought
it in the first place.

83
00:04:16.225 --> 00:04:18.725
My dad didn't have it in him.

84
00:04:18.750 --> 00:04:20.083
Whaddya mean?

85
00:04:20.108 --> 00:04:22.185
Your folks worked so hard.

86
00:04:22.187 --> 00:04:23.413
Yeah. they worked hard!

87
00:04:23.438 --> 00:04:26.255
They worked a lotta
hours for a lotta years.

88
00:04:26.280 --> 00:04:27.583
For nothin'.

89
00:04:27.608 --> 00:04:30.809
I dunno. Jimmy. He had a lotta
customers. Everybody liked him.

90
00:04:30.811 --> 00:04:34.177
Everybody liked him
'cause he was a soft touch.

91
00:04:34.202 --> 00:04:37.182
You know? Every deadbeat in
the neighborhood owed him money.

92
00:04:37.184 --> 00:04:38.817
You come in here with a sob story.

93
00:04:38.819 --> 00:04:41.620
you leave with a pat on the
back and a gallon of milk.

94
00:04:41.622 --> 00:04:43.221
He... he coulda made it work.

95
00:04:43.223 --> 00:04:45.023
He coulda sold beer and cigarettes

96
00:04:45.025 --> 00:04:46.825
to the kids from Mary-Margaret's.

97
00:04:46.827 --> 00:04:50.327
but... oh. no. not him.

98
00:04:50.352 --> 00:04:53.662
He was never gonna do what he had to do.

99
00:05:03.943 --> 00:05:05.811
How'd you know there'd be another?

100
00:05:10.302 --> 00:05:11.702
Oh.

101
00:05:11.727 --> 00:05:13.694
Banquet's over.

102
00:05:14.521 --> 00:05:18.022
Those conventioneers been
talking farm equipment

103
00:05:18.047 --> 00:05:20.181
for 10 hours straight...

104
00:05:20.206 --> 00:05:22.294
now they wanna party.

105
00:05:23.864 --> 00:05:26.864
Gonna be a big night.
my friend. Whaddya say?

106
00:05:26.889 --> 00:05:29.281
- Time to get moving?
- Let's go.

107
00:05:42.757 --> 00:05:47.710
<font color="#007700">Synced and corrected by Aaronnmb</font>
www.addic7ed.com

108
00:05:52.274 --> 00:05:54.474
_

109
00:09:18.534 --> 00:09:20.767
Yeah. Tribal police?

110
00:09:20.769 --> 00:09:23.970
Yeah. I was out on your
property this afternoon

111
00:09:23.972 --> 00:09:26.283
and found a dead body.

112
00:09:26.775 --> 00:09:29.267
Off the old post road.

113
00:09:29.292 --> 00:09:34.369
Out in the scrub. just past
the Oasis Motel billboard.

114
00:09:34.416 --> 00:09:38.618
I was out with my metal
detector. looking for arrowheads.

115
00:09:39.788 --> 00:09:41.245
No. I don't want to give my name.

116
00:09:41.270 --> 00:09:43.256
I-I-I was trespassing.

117
00:09:43.258 --> 00:09:45.565
Look. y-you'd better
send someone out there

118
00:09:45.590 --> 00:09:48.391
to find him before the coyotes do.

119
00:10:06.866 --> 00:10:11.241
Over here. I've recorded
the location of the incident.

120
00:10:11.266 --> 00:10:14.936
that is where I was
physically when it began.

121
00:10:14.938 --> 00:10:17.805
This column gives a proximate origin...

122
00:10:17.807 --> 00:10:20.093
uh. and as you can see. uh.

123
00:10:20.118 --> 00:10:23.611
much of time. I couldn't be
sure. so I just wrote "ambient."

124
00:10:23.613 --> 00:10:25.952
Um. and. of course.
I've recorded the. uh.

125
00:10:25.977 --> 00:10:28.149
times and dosages of the medicine.

126
00:10:28.151 --> 00:10:30.241
This is very impressive. Charles.

127
00:10:30.266 --> 00:10:32.882
And look at the trend!

128
00:10:33.280 --> 00:10:37.162
Day one. pain of 7 and 8. even 8.5.

129
00:10:37.187 --> 00:10:40.038
Day three. nothing higher
than five and a quarter.

130
00:10:40.063 --> 00:10:43.041
And now... it's all 3s and 4s.

131
00:10:43.734 --> 00:10:46.523
Later in the session. I'd
like to give you some exercises

132
00:10:46.548 --> 00:10:48.515
and strategies that
might help even more.

133
00:10:48.540 --> 00:10:50.004
I'm all ears.

134
00:10:50.757 --> 00:10:53.388
How do you see your next steps?

135
00:10:53.413 --> 00:10:56.844
Well. clearly. with
this kind of improvement.

136
00:10:56.846 --> 00:11:00.081
it won't be long before
I'm back to work full time.

137
00:11:00.083 --> 00:11:01.873
with no accommodations.

138
00:11:01.898 --> 00:11:04.229
And then. soon after. I
want to get back into court.

139
00:11:04.254 --> 00:11:06.820
I haven't argued a case
in almost three years.

140
00:11:06.845 --> 00:11:08.790
so that's next.

141
00:11:09.202 --> 00:11:12.484
And I'm gonna get these
lights turned back on.

142
00:11:12.509 --> 00:11:15.430
I want this house to be full of music.

143
00:11:15.432 --> 00:11:17.468
I want to have a dinner party...

144
00:11:17.493 --> 00:11:19.257
oh. hell. no.

145
00:11:19.282 --> 00:11:20.748
A great. big celebration.

146
00:11:20.773 --> 00:11:22.506
I want a hundred people in here.

147
00:11:22.531 --> 00:11:24.288
spilling out onto the lawn...

148
00:11:24.312 --> 00:11:27.190
I want caterers and a full bar.

149
00:11:28.163 --> 00:11:31.551
I want to be surrounded
by friends and colleagues.

150
00:11:31.553 --> 00:11:33.771
That's stirring.

151
00:11:33.796 --> 00:11:35.221
Those are excellent goals.

152
00:11:35.223 --> 00:11:37.148
Doctor. I wouldn't have believed

153
00:11:37.173 --> 00:11:40.334
I could come so far so quickly.

154
00:11:40.359 --> 00:11:43.507
And I have to give you the
lion's share of the credit.

155
00:11:43.532 --> 00:11:45.763
Well. it's remarkable.

156
00:11:45.788 --> 00:11:48.232
But Rome wasn't built in a day.

157
00:11:48.257 --> 00:11:50.290
I know rushing forward may be tempting.

158
00:11:50.292 --> 00:11:52.382
but it's important
to give yourself time.

159
00:11:52.384 --> 00:11:54.017
- Mm.
- You've just begun a journey

160
00:11:54.042 --> 00:11:56.854
that could take years.

161
00:11:57.979 --> 00:12:00.806
Well. I suppose. but. um.

162
00:12:00.808 --> 00:12:03.126
surely you'd admit that
every case is different?

163
00:12:03.151 --> 00:12:05.626
- Of course.
- Then perhaps. uh.

164
00:12:05.651 --> 00:12:07.553
my recovery might be speedier

165
00:12:07.555 --> 00:12:08.821
than your run-of-the-mill patient.

166
00:12:08.823 --> 00:12:09.987
Isn't that possible?

167
00:12:10.012 --> 00:12:12.158
I'm just cautioning you not
to push yourself too hard.

168
00:12:12.160 --> 00:12:13.602
- Mm.
- I know.

169
00:12:13.627 --> 00:12:15.995
Appreciate every step forward.

170
00:12:15.997 --> 00:12:18.364
but modulate your expectations.

171
00:12:18.366 --> 00:12:20.565
Yes. absolutely.

172
00:12:22.415 --> 00:12:24.770
Let's talk about the
night you first called me.

173
00:12:24.772 --> 00:12:26.572
- Mm.
- You sounded very distressed.

174
00:12:26.574 --> 00:12:28.107
I was.

175
00:12:28.109 --> 00:12:30.243
Using a telephone must
have been difficult for you.

176
00:12:31.579 --> 00:12:33.779
I had to walk 10 blocks to a pay phone.

177
00:12:33.781 --> 00:12:35.401
That was extremely uncomfortable.

178
00:12:35.426 --> 00:12:37.183
P-Probably almost a 9.

179
00:12:38.629 --> 00:12:42.026
What made it so important
to talk to me that night?

180
00:12:44.392 --> 00:12:46.674
I'd had an incident.

181
00:12:46.699 --> 00:12:50.065
A very public incident.

182
00:12:50.622 --> 00:12:53.932
Perhaps the worst experience of my life.

183
00:12:57.551 --> 00:13:00.354
It was proven to me.

184
00:13:00.379 --> 00:13:03.409
in public. and beyond
the shadow of a doubt.

185
00:13:03.411 --> 00:13:05.721
that there was a battery...

186
00:13:05.746 --> 00:13:08.447
a fully charged battery...

187
00:13:08.449 --> 00:13:12.557
almost next to my skin for
the better part of two hours.

188
00:13:13.721 --> 00:13:15.737
And I felt nothing.

189
00:13:18.127 --> 00:13:20.463
What does that mean to you?

190
00:13:24.612 --> 00:13:27.416
This condition...

191
00:13:28.436 --> 00:13:30.915
to me. it's as real as that chair.

192
00:13:30.940 --> 00:13:32.438
It's as real as this house.

193
00:13:32.440 --> 00:13:34.690
It's as real as you.

194
00:13:34.715 --> 00:13:36.348
But...

195
00:13:37.420 --> 00:13:39.994
what if it's not?

196
00:13:41.041 --> 00:13:43.596
What if it's all in my head?

197
00:13:44.852 --> 00:13:47.424
And if that's true...

198
00:13:48.623 --> 00:13:50.737
if it's not real...

199
00:13:53.315 --> 00:13:56.028
then what have I done?

200
00:14:03.004 --> 00:14:04.770
It's all in the storyboards.

201
00:14:04.772 --> 00:14:06.272
Get set for the master shot.

202
00:14:06.297 --> 00:14:07.696
Okay.

203
00:14:08.673 --> 00:14:10.978
Lookin' good! We about ready?

204
00:14:11.003 --> 00:14:13.112
- Just about.
- I gotta hand it to you.

205
00:14:13.114 --> 00:14:15.348
I mean. this is the busiest weekday

206
00:14:15.350 --> 00:14:17.049
we've had in the last six months.

207
00:14:17.051 --> 00:14:18.991
And are people
mentioning the commercial?

208
00:14:19.016 --> 00:14:20.712
You know what? They are.

209
00:14:20.737 --> 00:14:22.431
- Excellent!
- I know.

210
00:14:22.456 --> 00:14:23.656
Oh. here's your partner.

211
00:14:23.658 --> 00:14:26.125
Hey. get him into make-up.
and we can carve this turkey.

212
00:14:26.127 --> 00:14:27.385
Okay. Listen.

213
00:14:27.410 --> 00:14:29.385
L... Ex-excuse me. Not now.

214
00:14:29.410 --> 00:14:31.230
- It's all right.
- Sorry.

215
00:14:31.232 --> 00:14:33.466
I just got off the
phone with the station.

216
00:14:33.468 --> 00:14:35.134
You don't even work for them.

217
00:14:35.136 --> 00:14:36.702
I never said I work for the station.

218
00:14:36.704 --> 00:14:38.137
I...

219
00:14:38.650 --> 00:14:40.523
Saul Goodman Productions. remember?

220
00:14:40.548 --> 00:14:42.203
You work with us so
you don't have to deal

221
00:14:42.228 --> 00:14:44.033
with the bureaucrats at KWBV.

222
00:14:44.058 --> 00:14:45.524
We take care of everything.

223
00:14:45.549 --> 00:14:48.047
Okay. Remind me. how much
is all this gonna cost?

224
00:14:48.049 --> 00:14:50.422
Exactly what we talked
about the other day.

225
00:14:50.447 --> 00:14:52.865
The first one was
gratis. That's my treat.

226
00:14:52.897 --> 00:14:54.864
Now we're moving on
to the Elite package...

227
00:14:54.889 --> 00:14:58.154
seven commercials for the
heavily discounted price

228
00:14:58.179 --> 00:15:00.326
- of $6.500.
- Mm. Yeah.

229
00:15:00.328 --> 00:15:02.994
The station just quoted me $450 per.

230
00:15:03.019 --> 00:15:05.888
- $450?
- That's for air time only.

231
00:15:05.913 --> 00:15:07.600
Call the station.

232
00:15:07.602 --> 00:15:09.268
Ask them how much they'd charge

233
00:15:09.270 --> 00:15:12.279
for production of seven
top-flight TV commercials.

234
00:15:12.304 --> 00:15:13.939
Okay. but why do we need

235
00:15:13.941 --> 00:15:15.741
seven new ones in the first place?

236
00:15:15.743 --> 00:15:18.844
Yeah. What... what's to stop
us from paying the station

237
00:15:18.846 --> 00:15:20.568
to just keep running the one we have?

238
00:15:20.593 --> 00:15:22.348
That's not what we agreed to.

239
00:15:22.350 --> 00:15:24.912
How about that for starters?

240
00:15:26.435 --> 00:15:28.354
He did give us the first one for free.

241
00:15:28.356 --> 00:15:30.137
Yeah. I know.

242
00:15:30.162 --> 00:15:32.391
Okay. how about this...

243
00:15:32.928 --> 00:15:36.746
how about we pay you $450 for
the one that already aired.

244
00:15:36.771 --> 00:15:38.787
and then we take it from there?

245
00:15:38.818 --> 00:15:40.800
Guys. I don't wanna get technical on ya.

246
00:15:40.802 --> 00:15:43.769
but that commercial... it
doesn't actually belong to you.

247
00:15:43.794 --> 00:15:46.681
Look. it's the real and
intellectual property

248
00:15:46.706 --> 00:15:48.074
of Saul Goodman Productions.

249
00:15:48.076 --> 00:15:49.775
I don't think so.

250
00:15:49.777 --> 00:15:51.214
I mean. it's our faces.

251
00:15:51.239 --> 00:15:53.779
- It's our store.
- And it's my commercial.

252
00:15:53.781 --> 00:15:56.034
And you can't run it
without my permission.

253
00:15:56.036 --> 00:15:58.238
- Oh. Okay.
- Okay. Want to play it like that?

254
00:15:58.263 --> 00:15:59.269
- Mm-hmm.
- Okay...

255
00:15:59.294 --> 00:16:00.931
$450 is now off the table.

256
00:16:00.956 --> 00:16:03.026
- Yeah. and that crew of yours?
- Yeah.

257
00:16:03.051 --> 00:16:05.526
Just a bunch of UNM students.

258
00:16:05.551 --> 00:16:07.112
- We can get those.
- We can get students.

259
00:16:07.137 --> 00:16:08.316
- We can get students.
- Yes. we can.

260
00:16:08.341 --> 00:16:10.151
- We can reshoot the ad...
- Yes.

261
00:16:10.176 --> 00:16:11.574
- ... and then run that
- How about that?

262
00:16:11.599 --> 00:16:12.693
Guys. Guys. come on.

263
00:16:12.694 --> 00:16:14.526
Now. you wouldn't even be
thinking about a commercial

264
00:16:14.551 --> 00:16:15.753
if it wasn't for me!

265
00:16:15.778 --> 00:16:18.066
Okay. we are not gonna pay you $6.500

266
00:16:18.091 --> 00:16:19.495
for something that we can do ourselves.

267
00:16:19.520 --> 00:16:21.519
- You got it?
- Seriously?

268
00:16:21.544 --> 00:16:22.878
- Seriously.
- Seriously.

269
00:16:22.903 --> 00:16:24.362
- Th...
- Excuse us.

270
00:16:25.945 --> 00:16:28.862
Hello. there. Anything
we can help you with?

271
00:16:45.167 --> 00:16:47.827
- What?
- Put that camera back up. Roll it.

272
00:16:47.829 --> 00:16:50.113
- It's not gonna do a damn thing.
- Don't give me any lip. okay?

273
00:16:50.138 --> 00:16:53.573
Just roll it. Make sure
it's pointed in my direction.

274
00:16:58.440 --> 00:17:00.526
- Now. if you're gigging a lot...
- Are you gigging a lot?

275
00:17:00.551 --> 00:17:02.183
Uh. guys. Sorry to interrupt.

276
00:17:02.208 --> 00:17:04.474
Just want to make sure...
there's no wiggle room here?

277
00:17:04.499 --> 00:17:06.345
- We are with customers right now.
- Yeah.

278
00:17:06.347 --> 00:17:08.698
Please. all right? Just go. Thank you.

279
00:17:08.723 --> 00:17:11.503
Okay. well. best of luck in
all your future endeavors.

280
00:17:11.528 --> 00:17:13.152
- Go. Goodbye.
- Go.

281
00:17:13.154 --> 00:17:14.987
- Sorry about that.
- Sorry about that.

282
00:17:17.636 --> 00:17:18.923
Oh!

283
00:17:18.948 --> 00:17:21.298
Oh. my gosh! Are you okay?

284
00:17:21.323 --> 00:17:23.626
It was... a drumstick.

285
00:17:23.651 --> 00:17:25.737
It was laying loose in the aisle.

286
00:17:25.762 --> 00:17:29.035
- Somebody call an ambulance!
- No. you don't need to...

287
00:17:29.037 --> 00:17:31.183
I don't need...

288
00:17:31.208 --> 00:17:32.925
Aah!

289
00:17:32.950 --> 00:17:34.362
Yes. an ambulance.

290
00:17:34.387 --> 00:17:36.253
That's a good idea.

291
00:17:38.155 --> 00:17:41.214
You guys have liability
insurance. right?

292
00:17:42.541 --> 00:17:44.576
To our "Four Corners Strategy..."

293
00:17:44.601 --> 00:17:46.210
- Cheers to that.
- Cheers.

294
00:17:47.321 --> 00:17:48.481
Mmm.

295
00:17:48.506 --> 00:17:49.889
I'm not saying this to rush you.

296
00:17:49.914 --> 00:17:51.881
but I have a 2:45 tee
time at Four Hills...

297
00:17:51.906 --> 00:17:54.171
- so don't let me get. uh. long-winded.
- Okay.

298
00:17:54.196 --> 00:17:56.624
I've heard the water gets
tricky on the back nine there.

299
00:17:56.649 --> 00:17:58.755
You heard right. I
didn't know you played.

300
00:17:58.757 --> 00:18:00.123
Well. growing up where I did.

301
00:18:00.125 --> 00:18:01.866
there was pretty much
nothing else to do.

302
00:18:01.891 --> 00:18:04.127
We oughta be having this
meeting out on the fairway.

303
00:18:05.367 --> 00:18:07.533
Well. I think Kim has a lot to cover.

304
00:18:07.558 --> 00:18:08.717
Speaking of which...

305
00:18:08.742 --> 00:18:10.666
Sorry. but I-I gotta ask.

306
00:18:10.668 --> 00:18:12.101
I've got a friend. Billy Gatwood.

307
00:18:12.103 --> 00:18:15.605
He's a driller. has a small
operation over near Farwell.

308
00:18:15.607 --> 00:18:17.249
Anyway. the poor bastard's tangled up

309
00:18:17.274 --> 00:18:19.240
in some kind of an interstate wrangle

310
00:18:19.265 --> 00:18:20.665
between Texas and New Mexico.

311
00:18:20.690 --> 00:18:22.256
Now. I can't make heads or tails of it.

312
00:18:22.281 --> 00:18:23.647
and neither can he.

313
00:18:23.678 --> 00:18:25.317
His lawyer was a local guy.

314
00:18:25.342 --> 00:18:27.164
completely over his head.

315
00:18:27.197 --> 00:18:29.436
So Billy's fired the guy.
but now he doesn't know

316
00:18:29.461 --> 00:18:31.489
whether to shit or wind his watch...

317
00:18:31.514 --> 00:18:32.622
pardon my French.

318
00:18:32.624 --> 00:18:33.858
Right this way.

319
00:18:33.883 --> 00:18:36.241
Anyhow. I told him about
the job you're doing for us.

320
00:18:36.266 --> 00:18:37.897
and I know he'd love to talk to you.

321
00:18:37.922 --> 00:18:39.131
... Montana. I'd suggest Big Sky.

322
00:18:39.156 --> 00:18:40.522
It's got all the beauty of Montana.

323
00:18:40.547 --> 00:18:42.380
but you don't have to wait
as long in the lift lines.

324
00:18:42.405 --> 00:18:43.647
- Another...
- Oh. wow.

325
00:18:43.672 --> 00:18:45.702
I can't tell you how flattering that is.

326
00:18:45.727 --> 00:18:47.311
Remember. Kim's got her hands full

327
00:18:47.336 --> 00:18:49.647
with Utah and Colorado.

328
00:18:50.374 --> 00:18:52.296
As far as I'm concerned. she's proven

329
00:18:52.321 --> 00:18:55.064
she can field whatever we
throw at her and then some.

330
00:18:55.727 --> 00:18:58.530
Kevin. your faith in me is... it's...

331
00:18:58.850 --> 00:19:00.440
it means a lot.

332
00:19:00.465 --> 00:19:02.038
But when we first
started working together.

333
00:19:02.063 --> 00:19:04.427
I promised you Mesa Verde
would be my sole focus.

334
00:19:04.452 --> 00:19:05.569
And I meant it.

335
00:19:05.594 --> 00:19:07.427
- Well. sure. but I gotta take...
- Hey there!

336
00:19:07.452 --> 00:19:09.241
I thought I saw some familiar faces.

337
00:19:09.266 --> 00:19:10.960
- Howard.
- Kim... sit.

338
00:19:10.985 --> 00:19:12.605
I insist.

339
00:19:12.630 --> 00:19:14.171
- Kevin...
- Howard.

340
00:19:14.196 --> 00:19:16.365
... Paige... always
wonderful to see you.

341
00:19:16.367 --> 00:19:17.913
You. too. Howard. How've you been?

342
00:19:17.938 --> 00:19:19.569
Fantastic. Thank you.

343
00:19:19.571 --> 00:19:21.337
All's well with the expansion?

344
00:19:21.339 --> 00:19:22.952
I saw you got that branch approved

345
00:19:22.977 --> 00:19:24.600
on your original timeline. after all.

346
00:19:24.625 --> 00:19:26.817
We did. Thanks to Ms. Wexler here.

347
00:19:26.842 --> 00:19:28.999
Well. Kim's one of the best.
You're lucky to have her.

348
00:19:29.024 --> 00:19:30.830
She sure is. and we sure are.

349
00:19:30.855 --> 00:19:33.788
Seems like just yesterday she
was logging hours in doc review.

350
00:19:35.039 --> 00:19:36.892
Always a pleasure to see
one of our protégées

351
00:19:36.917 --> 00:19:39.397
spread her wings and leave the nest.

352
00:19:40.391 --> 00:19:42.223
Well. I'll get out of your hair.

353
00:19:42.248 --> 00:19:44.106
Best of luck to all of you.

354
00:19:44.131 --> 00:19:45.848
You. too. Howard.

355
00:19:48.075 --> 00:19:50.020
I appreciate that we've
got you all to ourselves.

356
00:19:50.045 --> 00:19:51.450
but I'm thinking Billy
just needs a consultation...

357
00:19:51.475 --> 00:19:54.005
I'm so sorry. um. but. uh.

358
00:19:54.030 --> 00:19:56.046
would you excuse me for just a moment?

359
00:19:56.071 --> 00:19:57.536
Sure.

360
00:20:19.373 --> 00:20:21.297
I've had the salmon here and the filet.

361
00:20:21.299 --> 00:20:22.889
if you like sea scallops.
they're fantastic.

362
00:20:22.914 --> 00:20:24.967
Kim. Uh. uh. hello again. Howard... sit.

363
00:20:24.969 --> 00:20:26.443
I insist. Sorry to interrupt.

364
00:20:26.468 --> 00:20:29.178
I just needed to give Howard something.

365
00:20:31.315 --> 00:20:33.686
Folks. this is Kim Wexler.

366
00:20:33.711 --> 00:20:35.278
a former member of our firm.

367
00:20:35.280 --> 00:20:37.818
Kim. uh. this is the team
from O'Malley Industries.

368
00:20:37.843 --> 00:20:39.448
Oh. of course. I remember Lauren.

369
00:20:39.450 --> 00:20:40.490
Good to see you again. Kim.

370
00:20:40.515 --> 00:20:42.036
This is Jack Sweet. our new CFO.

371
00:20:42.061 --> 00:20:43.327
- Oh. hello.
- Pleasure.

372
00:20:43.329 --> 00:20:44.995
Nice to see you. too. Henry. Nick.

373
00:20:44.997 --> 00:20:48.096
- Marie Austin. Good to meet you.
- Nice to meet you.

374
00:20:48.121 --> 00:20:50.121
Good to see all of you.

375
00:20:50.146 --> 00:20:52.475
- Have a wonderful lunch. Howard.
- Mm.

376
00:20:56.256 --> 00:20:57.874
Sorry to hold things up.

377
00:20:57.876 --> 00:20:59.645
- Not at all.
- Okay.

378
00:20:59.670 --> 00:21:01.678
Kevin. if you want to give
me Mr. Gatwood's number.

379
00:21:01.680 --> 00:21:03.180
I'd be happy to speak to him.

380
00:21:03.182 --> 00:21:04.514
Well. that's great.

381
00:21:04.516 --> 00:21:06.049
Once I understand what's going on.

382
00:21:06.051 --> 00:21:07.517
I'll put him together with a firm

383
00:21:07.519 --> 00:21:09.086
that'll take very good care of him.

384
00:21:09.088 --> 00:21:10.887
I leave it in your capable hands.

385
00:21:10.889 --> 00:21:13.082
Great. Okay. Utah.

386
00:21:13.107 --> 00:21:16.293
The good news is the filing
requirements are very similar

387
00:21:16.295 --> 00:21:18.462
- to what we submitted for Arizona.
- Oh. good.

388
00:21:18.464 --> 00:21:20.989
Thanks again. Kim. I'll let
Billy know you'll be calling.

389
00:21:21.014 --> 00:21:22.701
- and we'll talk tee times soon.
- Sounds good.

390
00:21:22.726 --> 00:21:24.701
- All right. Bye.
- See you soon. Kim.

391
00:21:24.703 --> 00:21:26.068
Thank you.

392
00:21:33.988 --> 00:21:35.454
What the hell is this?

393
00:21:35.479 --> 00:21:38.304
I think it's pretty self-explanatory.

394
00:21:39.695 --> 00:21:42.119
Look. Howard. you were very
generous when I left HHM.

395
00:21:42.121 --> 00:21:43.487
but it never sat right with me

396
00:21:43.489 --> 00:21:44.755
that you covered my law-school loans.

397
00:21:44.757 --> 00:21:46.655
It seemed to sit right at the time.

398
00:21:46.680 --> 00:21:48.279
I appreciate the gift.

399
00:21:48.304 --> 00:21:49.670
but now that I'm able to afford it.

400
00:21:49.695 --> 00:21:51.617
- I want to pay you back.
- Oh. you "appreciate the gift"?

401
00:21:51.642 --> 00:21:54.170
- Yes. I do. Howard.
- You know what I'm doing in there?

402
00:21:54.195 --> 00:21:55.953
Take a guess.

403
00:21:55.978 --> 00:21:57.667
I'm doing damage control.

404
00:21:57.669 --> 00:21:58.858
And I'm doing it three meals a day

405
00:21:58.883 --> 00:22:01.545
for the past two weeks with
every one of our clients.

406
00:22:01.570 --> 00:22:04.327
I'm busting my ass. trying to
repair the reputation of the firm

407
00:22:04.352 --> 00:22:06.743
after you and Jimmy
dragged it through the mud.

408
00:22:06.745 --> 00:22:08.779
I did everything in my
power to defend my client.

409
00:22:08.781 --> 00:22:10.347
Oh. is that what you're calling it?

410
00:22:10.372 --> 00:22:12.061
That's the job. Howard.

411
00:22:12.785 --> 00:22:14.684
And by the way. it was
all very convenient for you

412
00:22:14.686 --> 00:22:17.122
to ignore Chuck's illness
when it suited you.

413
00:22:17.147 --> 00:22:18.780
So. I take you out of the mail room.

414
00:22:18.805 --> 00:22:20.295
put you through law school. mentor you.

415
00:22:20.320 --> 00:22:22.259
and then when you leave and stab
me in the back. that's my fault?

416
00:22:22.261 --> 00:22:24.210
I'm not cashing this.

417
00:22:26.678 --> 00:22:29.599
Kim. your debt is forgiven.

418
00:22:29.601 --> 00:22:32.264
But anything else? That's on you.

419
00:22:32.638 --> 00:22:35.272
All Jimmy and I did was show
the situation for what it is.

420
00:22:35.274 --> 00:22:37.374
And if you are hiding
that from your clients?

421
00:22:37.376 --> 00:22:39.264
Well. Howard. that's on you.

422
00:25:14.226 --> 00:25:16.155
- Nacho.
- Hey. Papa.

423
00:25:16.180 --> 00:25:18.046
_

424
00:25:18.071 --> 00:25:22.460
_

425
00:25:22.485 --> 00:25:25.687
_

426
00:25:26.687 --> 00:25:28.781
_

427
00:25:29.320 --> 00:25:32.664
_

428
00:25:33.109 --> 00:25:34.765
_

429
00:25:41.836 --> 00:25:43.273
Blue shirt.

430
00:25:43.281 --> 00:25:45.077
Yellow wall.

431
00:25:45.102 --> 00:25:47.316
Silver door.

432
00:25:56.328 --> 00:25:58.038
White sign.

433
00:25:58.063 --> 00:26:00.030
Red pepper.

434
00:26:01.023 --> 00:26:02.890
Purple sweater.

435
00:26:03.242 --> 00:26:04.965
Brown wood.

436
00:26:04.990 --> 00:26:06.556
Black mat.

437
00:26:20.039 --> 00:26:21.672
Jason. can I get you to the front

438
00:26:21.674 --> 00:26:23.374
for carryout assistance?

439
00:26:23.376 --> 00:26:26.510
Jason to the front for
carryout assistance.

440
00:26:36.132 --> 00:26:37.849
Yellow bananas.

441
00:26:37.874 --> 00:26:39.490
Green grapes.

442
00:26:39.492 --> 00:26:42.293
Orange... oranges.

443
00:26:46.694 --> 00:26:48.271
Oh. excuse me.

444
00:26:48.296 --> 00:26:51.302
Um. where would I find the s-soy milk?

445
00:26:51.327 --> 00:26:54.484
Uh. over there and to the left.
just past the freezer aisle.

446
00:27:03.999 --> 00:27:06.171
_

447
00:27:13.726 --> 00:27:15.859
The white ceiling.

448
00:27:15.861 --> 00:27:17.528
Green basket.

449
00:27:17.530 --> 00:27:19.544
Gray floor.

450
00:27:45.218 --> 00:27:47.358
- All set?
- Yeah.

451
00:27:48.091 --> 00:27:49.408
Courier on the way?

452
00:27:49.433 --> 00:27:51.233
- 20 minutes.
- Great.

453
00:27:51.258 --> 00:27:54.294
They'll need this back
at Gatwood Oil by EOD.

454
00:27:56.711 --> 00:27:58.372
What's...?

455
00:28:06.802 --> 00:28:08.240
Hey.

456
00:28:08.242 --> 00:28:09.747
Hey.

457
00:28:15.263 --> 00:28:16.982
What's up?

458
00:28:16.984 --> 00:28:19.751
Oh. Uh. new guitar.

459
00:28:19.753 --> 00:28:21.519
Check it out.

460
00:28:23.536 --> 00:28:26.291
Mm. That is something.

461
00:28:26.293 --> 00:28:28.460
I sold the rest of my ads.

462
00:28:28.462 --> 00:28:30.677
- That must be a relief.
- Uh-huh.

463
00:28:30.702 --> 00:28:32.435
They loved the response they got.

464
00:28:32.460 --> 00:28:34.627
Were so impressed.
they threw in this baby.

465
00:28:34.652 --> 00:28:37.497
Signed by the one and
only Ritchie Blackmore.

466
00:28:38.013 --> 00:28:41.029
And. uh. lying on the floor

467
00:28:41.054 --> 00:28:43.325
helps you with your fingering?

468
00:28:43.350 --> 00:28:45.396
- Oh. I fell.
- What?

469
00:28:45.421 --> 00:28:47.402
It was during productions.

470
00:28:47.427 --> 00:28:48.989
Crazy stuff happens.

471
00:28:48.991 --> 00:28:50.424
A long story.

472
00:28:50.426 --> 00:28:53.794
But the big picture...
I'm up one guitar.

473
00:28:53.796 --> 00:28:55.583
When did this happen?

474
00:28:55.608 --> 00:28:56.697
Yesterday.

475
00:28:56.699 --> 00:28:58.432
I saw you yesterday. You were fine.

476
00:28:58.434 --> 00:29:00.434
Uh. that was Tuesday.

477
00:29:00.436 --> 00:29:03.497
You picked up clean clothes. 'Member?

478
00:29:04.473 --> 00:29:06.770
Did you go to the doctor?

479
00:29:07.825 --> 00:29:11.123
Oh. it's... it's not as bad as it looks.

480
00:29:11.125 --> 00:29:13.790
I just need to rest it. It'll be fine.

481
00:29:13.815 --> 00:29:15.481
Look on the desk.

482
00:29:15.506 --> 00:29:17.359
There's something for you.

483
00:29:19.221 --> 00:29:20.953
Yeah. that.

484
00:29:21.523 --> 00:29:22.812
Open it.

485
00:29:24.860 --> 00:29:26.633
That's my half.

486
00:29:26.658 --> 00:29:28.691
It's good for the next six weeks.

487
00:29:29.915 --> 00:29:32.499
So at least we can
stop talking about that.

488
00:29:32.501 --> 00:29:33.679
Jimmy. I wasn't...

489
00:29:33.704 --> 00:29:36.125
Just take it so we're square. all right?

490
00:29:37.640 --> 00:29:39.473
Okay.

491
00:29:40.404 --> 00:29:41.936
Sorry.

492
00:29:41.961 --> 00:29:46.246
Just... my back hurts
like hell. and. uh...

493
00:29:46.248 --> 00:29:49.082
people suck.

494
00:29:53.977 --> 00:29:55.672
Jimmy. you...

495
00:29:57.091 --> 00:29:59.945
you don't have to push
yourself like this.

496
00:30:03.032 --> 00:30:05.499
You could rest.

497
00:30:05.501 --> 00:30:07.206
Let your back heal.

498
00:30:07.231 --> 00:30:09.703
And then you go to community
service and get it over with.

499
00:30:09.705 --> 00:30:11.271
Take some time.

500
00:30:11.273 --> 00:30:13.240
Plan your next move.

501
00:30:13.242 --> 00:30:14.703
Meaning...?

502
00:30:14.728 --> 00:30:16.502
I'm saying...

503
00:30:16.527 --> 00:30:18.745
I could cover our expenses for a while.

504
00:30:18.770 --> 00:30:20.557
- Kim. you got the cash in your hand.
- Yeah. I know. but...

505
00:30:20.582 --> 00:30:22.124
- So why are we talking about this?
- All I'm saying is...

506
00:30:22.149 --> 00:30:24.184
I looked at the numbers.
and I can carry us.

507
00:30:24.186 --> 00:30:27.554
Not forever. but at least
until you're back to 100%.

508
00:30:27.556 --> 00:30:30.142
I appreciate the thought. but no.

509
00:30:30.167 --> 00:30:32.541
I'll do what I have to do
to take care of my half.

510
00:30:32.566 --> 00:30:34.695
You do what you have to
do to take care of yours.

511
00:30:34.697 --> 00:30:36.348
End of story.

512
00:30:40.039 --> 00:30:41.523
Okay.

513
00:30:46.181 --> 00:30:48.938
I mean. you believe me. right?

514
00:30:50.348 --> 00:30:51.958
Yes.

515
00:30:56.469 --> 00:30:58.458
Feel better. Jimmy.

516
00:31:17.269 --> 00:31:19.740
Francesca. is it too late
to get ahold of the courier?

517
00:31:19.742 --> 00:31:21.767
I can call. Need to reschedule?

518
00:31:21.792 --> 00:31:23.343
No. cancel it.

519
00:31:23.345 --> 00:31:25.579
And get Billy Gatwood
on the phone for me.

520
00:31:25.581 --> 00:31:27.402
- Will do.
- Thanks.

521
00:31:33.386 --> 00:31:35.756
I've got Billy Gatwood on the line.

522
00:31:36.726 --> 00:31:38.847
Great. Put him through.

523
00:31:42.431 --> 00:31:44.631
Mr. Gatwood? Hi. Kim Wexler.

524
00:31:44.656 --> 00:31:46.767
Listen. I've been
reviewing your documents.

525
00:31:46.769 --> 00:31:50.053
and I thought I might've had to
refer you to a colleague. but...

526
00:31:50.078 --> 00:31:52.662
I think I may have a solution
to your problem myself.

527
00:31:52.687 --> 00:31:54.775
Do you think you have
some time this week

528
00:31:54.777 --> 00:31:56.543
we could sit down and talk?

529
00:32:00.766 --> 00:32:02.915
- Chuck.
- Howard.

530
00:32:02.940 --> 00:32:04.365
What a nice surprise.

531
00:32:04.367 --> 00:32:06.853
I knocked. but there was no
answer. Thought you were asleep.

532
00:32:06.855 --> 00:32:08.989
Figured I'd wait. in case...

533
00:32:08.991 --> 00:32:11.592
Are those groceries? They are.

534
00:32:11.617 --> 00:32:13.994
I decided to go for a little walk.

535
00:32:13.996 --> 00:32:16.121
- That's great. Chuck.
- Why don't you come on in?

536
00:32:16.146 --> 00:32:17.492
Uh. thank you.

537
00:32:18.703 --> 00:32:20.444
To what do I owe the pleasure?

538
00:32:20.469 --> 00:32:22.613
Well. I wish it was just a social call.

539
00:32:22.638 --> 00:32:24.953
but unfortunately. we do have
an issue we need to discuss.

540
00:32:24.978 --> 00:32:26.311
What's that?

541
00:32:26.336 --> 00:32:28.708
It concerns your malpractice insurance.

542
00:32:28.710 --> 00:32:30.043
There's...

543
00:32:31.180 --> 00:32:34.219
well. we should sit and talk it through.

544
00:33:39.722 --> 00:33:42.760
_

545
00:34:15.634 --> 00:34:17.391
You're good.

546
00:34:17.738 --> 00:34:19.104
Cool.

547
00:34:19.661 --> 00:34:21.761
See you. Nacho.

548
00:34:24.927 --> 00:34:26.886
Don Hector.

549
00:34:58.379 --> 00:34:59.815
What?

550
00:35:02.284 --> 00:35:04.268
This one looks funny.

551
00:35:08.713 --> 00:35:10.471
Bring it here.

552
00:35:26.422 --> 00:35:28.054
You see? Is it fake?

553
00:35:33.055 --> 00:35:35.407
No. it's fine.

554
00:35:40.282 --> 00:35:42.469
I'm so sorry. Don Hector.

555
00:36:39.194 --> 00:36:42.295
- Carlos.
- Nacho.

556
00:36:51.606 --> 00:36:53.573
I'm heavy.

557
00:36:53.575 --> 00:36:55.842
Took care of that problem over on Fifth.

558
00:36:55.844 --> 00:36:57.944
That crew won't bother us no more...

559
00:36:57.946 --> 00:37:00.131
Hey. do me a favor. Shut up.

560
00:37:05.912 --> 00:37:07.779
You're good.

561
00:37:07.804 --> 00:37:09.615
Okay.

562
00:37:11.193 --> 00:37:13.248
See you next week.

563
00:38:58.338 --> 00:39:00.611
Don Hector. more espresso?

564
00:39:57.204 --> 00:39:59.085
McGill.

565
00:39:59.111 --> 00:40:01.346
Keep it moving.

566
00:40:10.620 --> 00:40:13.181
- Sir. Sir.
- What's up?

567
00:40:13.206 --> 00:40:15.990
Hey. uh. it's... it's my kid.

568
00:40:15.992 --> 00:40:17.425
Her mom just called.

569
00:40:17.427 --> 00:40:19.393
You're not supposed to be on the phone.

570
00:40:19.395 --> 00:40:20.895
I know. I know. but she's sick.

571
00:40:20.897 --> 00:40:22.329
She caught pneumonia at day care.

572
00:40:22.331 --> 00:40:24.244
She's in the hospital. Please. can I go?

573
00:40:24.269 --> 00:40:26.633
Sure. you can go. But
you're not gettin' credit.

574
00:40:26.636 --> 00:40:28.985
C'mon. can I just go
and come right back?

575
00:40:29.010 --> 00:40:31.105
I have to get my hours done this week.

576
00:40:31.130 --> 00:40:32.494
Judge says so.

577
00:40:32.519 --> 00:40:34.275
Judge told you. huh?

578
00:40:34.277 --> 00:40:36.277
Sounds like that's on you.

579
00:40:50.367 --> 00:40:52.062
Hey. buddy. you wanna get outta here?

580
00:40:52.087 --> 00:40:54.922
- How much is it worth to you?
- What?

581
00:40:54.947 --> 00:40:56.713
To ditch this.

582
00:40:56.738 --> 00:40:59.765
- How much?
- Leave me alone. yo.

583
00:41:00.148 --> 00:41:02.670
Come on. You want to
get to your deal or what?

584
00:41:02.672 --> 00:41:05.037
Man. I was just tryin'
ta see my sick kid.

585
00:41:06.109 --> 00:41:07.842
You're trying to sell
something you shouldn't have

586
00:41:07.844 --> 00:41:09.951
to someone who shouldn't be buying it.

587
00:41:09.976 --> 00:41:12.911
Hey. No judgments. all right?

588
00:41:12.936 --> 00:41:16.272
Man's gotta make a living. I'm just
saying the way you make yours...

589
00:41:16.297 --> 00:41:18.405
rhymes with "mug mealer."

590
00:41:18.430 --> 00:41:20.077
Yeah. What are you... a narc?

591
00:41:20.102 --> 00:41:21.801
I'm the guy who's gonna
get you out of here

592
00:41:21.826 --> 00:41:23.976
- and let you keep your hours.
- Yeah?

593
00:41:24.001 --> 00:41:25.493
- Yeah.
- How you gonna do that?

594
00:41:25.495 --> 00:41:27.710
Lemme worry about the how. okay?

595
00:41:27.735 --> 00:41:29.463
You just...

596
00:41:29.465 --> 00:41:32.021
700 bucks. and you're gone.

597
00:41:32.046 --> 00:41:34.368
No. I don't have 700 bucks.

598
00:41:34.370 --> 00:41:37.705
Hey. you got a couple
grand in your sock.

599
00:41:41.043 --> 00:41:42.676
700 bucks.

600
00:41:42.678 --> 00:41:44.608
And you can get me outta here?

601
00:41:46.260 --> 00:41:47.560
Aight.

602
00:41:47.585 --> 00:41:49.483
You can do it. you got a deal.

603
00:41:50.702 --> 00:41:53.888
Okay. Just go pick up trash. Go on.

604
00:42:11.707 --> 00:42:14.141
The hell's this?

605
00:42:15.745 --> 00:42:18.646
Resting. Uh. hurt my back.

606
00:42:18.648 --> 00:42:20.147
Get up.

607
00:42:20.149 --> 00:42:23.150
Nope. My back's killing me.

608
00:42:23.152 --> 00:42:24.518
Suit yourself.

609
00:42:24.520 --> 00:42:26.368
You're not getting your hours.

610
00:42:26.393 --> 00:42:29.327
I'm pretty sure you're
gonna give me my hours.

611
00:42:29.352 --> 00:42:30.938
Oh. yeah?

612
00:42:30.963 --> 00:42:32.730
And how do you figure that?

613
00:42:32.755 --> 00:42:35.118
'Cause if you don't. I'm gonna sue you.

614
00:42:36.393 --> 00:42:38.709
Hate to break it to you. smart guy.

615
00:42:38.734 --> 00:42:40.454
but you signed a waiver.

616
00:42:40.479 --> 00:42:42.545
I signed a waiver with the city.

617
00:42:42.570 --> 00:42:44.538
But I'm not suing the city.

618
00:42:44.540 --> 00:42:47.259
I'm suing you! Personally!

619
00:42:49.798 --> 00:42:51.712
You can't do that.

620
00:42:52.376 --> 00:42:53.929
Buddy...

621
00:42:56.946 --> 00:42:59.353
this is the land of the free
and the home of the lawsuit...

622
00:42:59.355 --> 00:43:00.955
I sure as shootin' can.

623
00:43:00.957 --> 00:43:02.356
And you know what?

624
00:43:02.381 --> 00:43:05.470
I think I'll bring that guy in with me

625
00:43:05.495 --> 00:43:07.761
and make it a class-action thing.

626
00:43:07.763 --> 00:43:09.314
What's he got to do with it?

627
00:43:09.339 --> 00:43:12.806
You knowingly prevented him from
visiting his child in the hospital.

628
00:43:12.831 --> 00:43:17.337
If that isn't intentional infliction
of emotional distress. what is?

629
00:43:17.362 --> 00:43:19.118
That's... crazy.

630
00:43:19.143 --> 00:43:20.751
Crazy hasn't even started.

631
00:43:20.776 --> 00:43:24.211
I can also sue you for failure to
approve community-service hours...

632
00:43:24.213 --> 00:43:26.665
that's a direct violation of your duties

633
00:43:26.690 --> 00:43:28.756
as an agent of the state of New Mexico.

634
00:43:28.781 --> 00:43:30.361
I'm only doin' my job...

635
00:43:30.386 --> 00:43:32.886
And just for tickles. maybe I throw in

636
00:43:32.911 --> 00:43:36.590
failure to treat and mitigate
damages suffered by me

637
00:43:36.592 --> 00:43:38.532
due to injuries sustained
under your watch.

638
00:43:38.557 --> 00:43:40.227
- Injury?
- My back.

639
00:43:40.229 --> 00:43:41.759
You're full of shit.

640
00:43:41.784 --> 00:43:43.597
- The waiver clearly states...
- Now. that waiver's

641
00:43:43.599 --> 00:43:46.400
gonna make Swiss cheese look solid.

642
00:43:46.402 --> 00:43:50.001
And in a personal lawsuit.
it's a fart in the wind.

643
00:43:51.607 --> 00:43:53.941
You're never gonna win that.

644
00:43:53.943 --> 00:43:55.953
Maybe. Maybe not.

645
00:43:55.978 --> 00:43:59.212
In order to find out. we
gotta do some math. Let's see.

646
00:43:59.237 --> 00:44:01.361
A lawyer's gonna cost you
about 90 bucks an hour.

647
00:44:01.386 --> 00:44:05.188
You're looking at 8 to 12
months of litigation. minimum.

648
00:44:05.665 --> 00:44:07.265
I'll represent myself.

649
00:44:07.290 --> 00:44:08.822
Great! Bring it on.

650
00:44:08.824 --> 00:44:10.357
You got a car? You got a house?

651
00:44:10.359 --> 00:44:12.890
A pension? Kiss it all goodbye.

652
00:44:12.915 --> 00:44:16.430
Look. out here. you might
be King Douche-nozzle.

653
00:44:16.432 --> 00:44:20.157
but in court. you are little people.

654
00:44:20.182 --> 00:44:21.689
Look. the judge and I...

655
00:44:21.714 --> 00:44:24.348
we'll gladly spend the next
five years in the courtroom.

656
00:44:24.373 --> 00:44:25.626
But for you. it's expensive.

657
00:44:25.651 --> 00:44:27.611
It's very. very expensive.

658
00:44:27.636 --> 00:44:29.904
It's third-mortgage expensive.

659
00:44:29.929 --> 00:44:33.787
So... I'm offering you a simple choice.

660
00:44:33.812 --> 00:44:35.231
You can go to your wife.

661
00:44:35.256 --> 00:44:37.451
You can explain to her
you're about to lose your job.

662
00:44:37.453 --> 00:44:40.373
your pension. and whatever
pinhole of a reputation

663
00:44:40.398 --> 00:44:43.099
you've got at the bowling
alley on Glow-ball Sundays.

664
00:44:43.124 --> 00:44:47.504
or let my friend here visit his
sick daughter in the hospital.

665
00:44:47.529 --> 00:44:49.063
and you can let me rest my back

666
00:44:49.065 --> 00:44:53.467
on this sacred. now
litter-free New Mexico soil.

667
00:44:53.469 --> 00:44:56.236
Oh. and we keep our hours.

668
00:45:03.116 --> 00:45:04.865
Fine.

669
00:45:06.046 --> 00:45:07.912
Asshole.

670
00:45:12.086 --> 00:45:13.953
Well. go on!

671
00:45:14.391 --> 00:45:16.490
Get outta here.

672
00:45:18.094 --> 00:45:19.393
Hey. man.

673
00:45:19.395 --> 00:45:22.896
That was some Jedi
mind shit right there!

674
00:45:28.204 --> 00:45:31.204
The best $700 I done ever spent.

675
00:45:36.128 --> 00:45:37.745
Here you go.

676
00:45:37.747 --> 00:45:39.104
I'm out.

677
00:45:43.620 --> 00:45:45.252
Yeah. yeah.

678
00:45:45.254 --> 00:45:47.721
Yo. I'm on my way. Yeah. yeah.

679
00:46:48.984 --> 00:46:51.846
I've got a problem I
think you can help me with.

680
00:46:51.871 --> 00:46:54.471
I've got cash I can't spend.

681
00:46:54.790 --> 00:46:57.697
About $200.000.

682
00:46:58.244 --> 00:46:59.993
If anything happens to me.

683
00:46:59.995 --> 00:47:02.650
my family'll never see it.

684
00:47:03.999 --> 00:47:07.189
Now. it seems to me
you opened this place

685
00:47:07.214 --> 00:47:10.158
to solve a similar problem.

686
00:47:11.260 --> 00:47:16.210
And you think that solution
could be applied to you.

687
00:47:16.212 --> 00:47:18.853
As a one-time arrangement.

688
00:47:20.836 --> 00:47:24.151
It would be unwise for us
to be publicly associated.

689
00:47:24.153 --> 00:47:25.766
wouldn't you agree?

690
00:47:26.688 --> 00:47:28.622
Because of the Salamancas.

691
00:47:28.624 --> 00:47:30.724
If they were to take notice.

692
00:47:30.726 --> 00:47:34.532
there would be
consequences for both of us.

693
00:47:38.680 --> 00:47:41.532
I'm thinking a paper transaction.

694
00:47:41.557 --> 00:47:43.110
Even so.

695
00:47:46.344 --> 00:47:48.375
Perhaps there is a way.

696
00:47:49.048 --> 00:47:51.876
One with a degree more...

697
00:47:51.901 --> 00:47:53.667
difficulty.

698
00:47:53.692 --> 00:47:56.485
But one I may be able to arrange.

699
00:47:58.020 --> 00:48:01.622
Would 20% overcome this difficulty?

700
00:48:03.089 --> 00:48:05.904
I would not take money from your family.

701
00:48:18.977 --> 00:48:22.610
